There are many different data repositories available online. The secondary resources table on the Books and Resources page found on the Course website includes many such repositories. 3b)¶

Next, let's practice using the .groupby().aggregate() "chain" to apply summary functions to specific columns grouped by grouping variables. Specifically, you must group by the country column and calculate two summary statistics. The number of rows (size) for each unique value of country must be named num_rows in a new Pandas DataFrame. Secondly, the number of unique values of variety for each unique value of country must be named total_varities.

Assign the result to the country_info object. The country column must be "regular" column and not the .index attribute associated with the new summarized DataFrame.

3b) - SOLUTION¶

In [ ]:
country_info=wine.groupby(['country']).\
aggregate(num_rows=('country','size'),
           total_varieties=('variety','nunique')
           )
